  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Use the boundary line",
      "content": "The boundary line is\n$$rx+ty=-77$$\nTwo clear points on it are $(0,-11)$ and $(-7,-10)$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Find r plus t",
      "content": "Substitute $(0,-11)$:\n$$0r-11t=-77$$\n$$t=7$$\nSubstitute $(-7,-10)$:\n$$-7r-10(7)=-77$$\n$$-7r-70=-77$$\n$$r=1$$\nTherefore,\n$$r+t=1+7=8$$\nThe answer is <strong>A</strong>."
    }
  ]
}
